[{'text': '7,"16q24.3 microdeletion syndrome","A chromosomal deletion syndrome caused by the loss of a segment of chromosome 16q24.3, resulting in a variable phenotype that often includes developmental delay, intellectual disability, and dysmorphic features.","NAN",6,6,"MONDO:0016838",1,"16q24.3 microdeletion syndrome","Developmental delay","Intellectual disability","Dysmorphic features","Feeding difficulties","Hypotonia","Seizures","Heart defects","Growth retardation","NAN","The symptoms vary, but developmental delay and intellectual disability are common.  Dysmorphic features can include facial anomalies, limb abnormalities, and heart defects.","The syndrome is caused by a deletion in the 16q24.3 region of chromosome 16.  The size of the deletion can vary, leading to differing severity of symptoms.","De novo deletion","NAN","NAN","NAN","NAN","Supportive care","Physical therapy","Occupational therapy","Genetic counseling","Prenatal testing","NAN","NAN","Variable, often in infancy or early childhood","Deletion of genes in the 16q24.3 region","Often sporadic, but can be inherited","Variable, depending on the size of the deletion and the specific genes affected","Chromosomal microarray analysis","Heart defects, feeding difficulties, and seizures","Rare","Variable, depends on the severity and specific complications."\n'}]